   </info>
   <refnamediv>
       <refname>polymult</refname>
               <refpurpose>mimics gauss function polymult </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>vecout=polymult(vec1,vec2)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> vec1 </term> =    a (nx1) vector of coefficients representing a polynom</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> vec2 </term> =    a (mx1) vector of coefficients representing a polynom</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> vecout </term> =    a ((n+m)x1) vector of coefficients representing a polynom</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function that mimics gauss function polymult: polymult = Scilab function convol ! (but with greater precision) 

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
polymult([1 2 1],[1 -2])// returns
//ans  =//!   1.    0.  - 3.  - 2. !  

               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
